Loop Controls:- if you have a block of code which you want to use it repetedly then we use a loop control. In java there are following types of loop controls:-

1.while loop
1.for loop
1.do hile loop
1.for-each loop

While loop:- While is a keyword which works as a loop control.

Syntax:-
// initilization of loop counter;
// int x;
while(condition) {
    //code
    //incrementation => update the loop counter
}

Ex: 
int c = 1;
while(c <= 5) {
    System.out.println(c);
    c++;
}
